Faustine wrote:

> Have you happened to have seen any good
> papers on constructing do-it-yourself cheap,
> effective, portable shielding?

Here's a company that sells tempest shielded "tents":

http://www.bemashield.com/seseries.html

This a site that has all sorts of tempest links:

http://www.eskimo.com/~joelm/tempestsource.html

With a bit more searching, you can find a company that manufactures the
material used in the tents (I'd try 3M).  Then, if you're handy with a
sewing machine and can find the appropriate Simplicity pattern, you're in
business.


